summary:
Bhavin is an accomplished information technology professional with more than sixteen years diversified experience as a manager and team leader with one of the industry’s leading players. Consistently tasked with leading projects in emerging technologies, Bhavin has been working with the next generation of mmWave/RF/radar sensors since 2015.

Bhavin is an experienced project manager with a proven history of bringing projects to successful and satisfactory completion. He is able to balance the requirements of the customer with those of the company to provide the best possible outcome. Bhavin's expertise includes:
•	developing, testing and validating products in the wireless and small cell base station markets;
•	designing and developing products incorporating multi-core processors with ADCs and DACs for the industrial, medical, avionics, and test and measurement markets;
•	implementing product security;
•	defining and validating power management strategies for industry standard PoE+ compliance.

projects.description:
Led the team responsible for the electrical characterization of peripherals for the TCI6630K2L device. The team developed an innovative way of performing DDR and PCIe characteristics on an existing board and limited changes on that board for the characterization of high-speed peripherals.
This resulted in:
•	a saving of four to five person-months;
•	a saving of $200,000 to $300,000 in new board development costs;
•	generating more than seven new documentations in a year for the Lamarr release to market.
